description:
Every year, hundreds of thousands of pilgrims join the Baishatun Mazu pilgrimage in Taiwan. But the journey is as challenging as it is unpredictable, because at every intersection along the 400 km walk the sea goddess herself is believed to decide which way her divine palanquin will turn.

We followed Mazu’s ever-changing route to discover how modern technology is transforming one of Taiwan’s most remarkable religious traditions.

@baishatun_tv

#guqin #selftaught

My self-teaching path with chinese traditional instrument guqin.

Pieces and songs I play throughout the video:

00:46 1 month: 小白菜;
01:12 2,3 months: 初见, Goodbye My Princess (东宫);
01:52 4 months: To Love's End, InuYasha;
02:12 5 months: 不染, Ashes of Love;
02:42 8 months: 凉凉;
03:06 10 months: SDAIAY;
03:20 11 months: 酒狂 and 忘忧;
04:21 1 year: 沧海一声笑 from Swordsman;
04:47 1 year 1 month: Last Dance, 伍佰;
05:20 1 year 2 months: 凉凉;
05:55 1 year 3 months: 一拜天地;
06:30 1 year 4 months: 凉凉;
07:08 1 year 5 months: with bow - Frostpunk Theme;
07:16 1 year 8 months: 平沙落雁;
08:01 1 year 10 months: 采茶调;
08:28 1 year 11 months: Oh, my darling Clementine;
08:48 2 years: 梅花三弄;
